    Scope and Contents
COAL MINING AND UNION ACTIVITIES PROJECT
Poole, coal miner, discusses mine wars and unions from the 1920's  through the 40's: PMA, UMW, prohibition, Charlie Birger and bootleggers, Eldorado and other southern Illinois towns, and his work in the mines.1 tape, 90 mins., 27 pp.
Interview by Rex Rhodes, 1972
